Change an existing model:
  Add a column:
      rails generate migration add_to_$MYTABLE
    In the new db/migrate/$TIMESTAMP_add_to_$MYTABLE.rb :
      add_column :$MYTABLE, :$MYCOLUMN, :$TYPE 
    In app/controllers $MY_TABLE_controller.rb add :$MYCOLUMN to the params of 
      params.require(:$MYTABLE).permit
    In app/views/$MYTABLE add your COLUMN to ever required occurence in _form.html.erb, index.html.erb and show.html.erb
    In test/controllers/$MY_TABLE_controller_test.rb add :$MYCOLUMN to
      post :create, customer: { }
    in 'test "should create customer" do' and to 
      patch :update, id: @customer, customer: { }
    in 'test "should update customer" do'.
      rails s
    (Of course this only changes the stuff generated by generate scaffold)
  Change a column type:
      rails generate migration change_format_in_$MYTABLE
    In the new db/migrate/$TIMESTAMP_change_format_in_$MYTABLE.rb :
      change_column :$MYTABLE, :$MYCOLUMN, :$TYPE
    Now you only need to change the files in app/views/$MYTABLE
  Remove a column:
      rails generate migration remove_from_$MYTABLE
    In the new db/migrate/$TIMESTAMP_remove_from_$MYTABLE.rb :
      remove_column :$MYTABLE, :$MYCOLUMN
    Remove all references to $MYCOLUMN (from the files refernced in "Add a column")
